# Next — Targeting Q4 kick-off

Scoped but not started. Will be refined at Jul 14 sync.

## swift-music 0.4
- Chord voicing engine (`Chord.voicings(for:range:)`)
- MIDI export via CoreMIDI (Darwin only, `#if canImport(Darwin)`)
- Estimated: **3 weeks** of eng

## swift-env 2.0 — breaking
- Drop `@EnvVar` in favour of `@AppDependency` pattern (see [[z=2|Later]])
- Typed throws on `resolve(_:)` — internal API only per conventions
- Migration guide needed before tagging beta

## swift-ascii 1.2
- Voxel grid renderer (feeds 3md blend view — eat our own cooking)
- `ASCIICanvas.snapshot() -> String` for test assertions
- Estimated: **1.5 weeks**

> **Decision needed:** swift-music CoreMIDI dependency breaks Linux target. Ship as Darwin-only or use virtual MIDI stub?

