Documented here so we stop re-proposing them.

| Idea | Why Cut | Cut Date |
|------|---------|----------|
| swift-combine wrapper | Swift 6 Concurrency supersedes it; Linux non-starter | 2026-04-10 |
| Vapor integration layer | Scope creep; Vapor team ships their own | 2026-05-02 |
| swift-cache Redis backend | `Bun.redis` covers the web use case; Swift server market too small | 2026-06-01 |
| Objective-C bridging headers | Contradicts zero-dependency philosophy | 2026-06-15 |

> If you want to resurrect anything here, write a one-pager and bring it to the next planning sync. "We should do X" without a doc goes back on this list.

@plane z=4 label="Principles"
# Roadmap Principles

These govern every scoping decision. Non-negotiable.

**Zero dependencies by default.**
Every new library ships with no third-party deps. Optional integrations go in separate targets.

**Platforms first, features second.**
If it doesn't pass CI on Linux and Windows, it doesn't ship. Add `#if canImport(Darwin)` gates, not exceptions.

**Breaking changes need a migration guide.**
Tag `-rc.1` at least 2 weeks before `1.0` or any major bump. No surprise majors.

**Async/await everywhere.**
No completion handlers in any public API, ever. New code that introduces callbacks is rejected at review — `fledge review` will flag it.

**Ship it or cut it.**
Anything sitting in "Next" for two consecutive quarters without a champion moves to "Cut List" automatically.

